WEBVTT

00:03:29.086 --> 00:03:32.149
MB: And so for a long time we are taught

00:03:32.173 --> 00:03:36.015
that we should be zeroing in
on our weaknesses in some --

00:03:36.039 --> 00:03:38.118
now, that's remediation.

00:03:38.142 --> 00:03:41.277
AG: Remediation: the idea
that we can examine our weaknesses

00:03:41.301 --> 00:03:43.609
and take concrete steps to fix them.

00:03:43.633 --> 00:03:47.152
MB: We live in a remedial world.
All apologies to Madonna.

00:03:47.176 --> 00:03:48.358
AG: (Laughs)

00:03:48.382 --> 00:03:50.577
MB: But we are living in a remedial world.

00:03:50.601 --> 00:03:52.545
AG: But remediation is really just a way

00:03:52.569 --> 00:03:56.593
to help people go from bad to average
at a particular activity.

00:03:56.617 --> 00:03:59.968
MB: You don't remediate
your way to excellence.